                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">If you are good at charming, there is no reason to solo with your animation. You can do it, but it is much slower.
<br />

<br />
I primarily use my animation when I am grouped and will not be charming. It doesn't hurt to have it out. I usually try to get aggro for just a second. It's easy to do this. Enchanters should know about when they can cast Tash, and not be aggro'd. (usually around 95% depending on where you are) So I tash at 95% and then go sit next to the mob. The tank keeps aggro til I sit. As soon as I get hit, I stand back up and the tank gets aggro again. I always keep a rune up so the cleric doesn't need to heal me.
<br />

<br />
That's the main use I have found for my animation at level 55 anyway.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Marteeny
<br />
56 Enchanter
<br />
Vazaelle</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
