                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Goner is good for things like:
<br />
-reclaim energy after rez for a little extra mana (hitpoint buffs for Goner help)
<br />
-mass tradeskill farming (agro lots of trash mobs and let goner have at 'em.)
<br />
-agro (or fear) kiting (partner with a ranger, snare + fear, at which point you tell the ranger to keep up with Goner).
<br />
-posing for picture, if you really want to look different from that wizard in the screenshot, summon goner to help you look more important.
<br />

<br />
However, using goner regularly for exp is probably not recommended.  We're enchanters, not mages, not necros.  If we want a pet, we go find one.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=378985" target="_blank" class="postlink">Tashim</a>, 65th Enchanter
<br />
<a href="http://www.drow.org/" target="_blank" class="postlink">Blood of the Spider</a>, <a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency" target="_blank" class="postlink">The Rathe</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
